@NODE "Mail_60" "Re: A few questions"
From: Tim Hanson <msinister@connectfree.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 15 Feb 1999 21:33:54 -0000
Subject: Re: A few questions

On 16-Feb-99, James L Boyd wrote:
>Well, this is my sin/cos/plotting a circle routine...it's not great,
>but it's the best I can do :)

It`s a good accurate routine. You can speed it up on slower machines by using
look up tables. But has everyone seen this routine?

WbToScreen 0
Window 0,0,0,320,256,0,"",0,1


DEFTYPE.q x,y

x=120
y=0

WPlot x,y,0
For i=0 To 200
    x-y/25
    y+x/25
    WPlot x+160,y+128,1
Next

It`s very inaccurate (infact it draws a very shallow spiral) but with tweeking
and different values depending on your needs it can be very quick.

Tim Hanson
in the Basement,London.



@ENDNODE
