On 24 Feb 99, at 15:55, Paul Burkey wrote:

> released this stuff. There`s certainly a BIG non-standard thing
> going on regarding different versions of acidlibs. Mine is
> 272,860 bytes long.

That could be the third parameter problem with Blitz functions, most likel=
y as 
its normally OS newtypes that have a hand in it. Julian Kinraid wrote a fi=
x for 
it, I've attached his mail to the bottom of this message (and the files yo=
u 
need).

> > PS - The included sound is cartman from SouthPark,
> > if that helps :o)

> Kick ass! :)

 Oh my god, they killed Burkey!!! ;)

-------------- Julian's message

There is a bug in Blitz, that appears when a Statement/Function with
more than three parameters has to allocate more than 4 bytes for a
variable.  This is an example -

Statement test{one.w, two.w, three.w, four.w}
    DEFTYPE.Gadget gad

    Nprint three
End Statement

test{1,2,3,4}

The output of this program might be '65534'.

The good news is that it can be fixed.  Firstly, BACKUP your
blitz2:acidlibs file.  Then unarchive the included file to ram:.  Open a
shell and type -

CD Ram:
Changelib PROGDIR: staticslib.obj

Begone bug! (don't type that :)

--
Julian Kinraid
