Subject: Re: Compiled/Executable?

John Mason churned out *this* drivel :
> 
> > Is there a way to find out if the code being run is an executable
or if
> > it's just been run from within Blitz?  I'd like to have my program
read

Ok, as a bare bones skeleton:

If FromCli
	If NumPars>0
		Parse command line parameters
	else
		use defaults
	end if
else
	If tooltypes exist ;This can be done using one of the tooltypes
commands
		Read and use
	else
		use defaults
	endif
endif

	Thom
