> > While on this sort of topic though, does anyone know how blitz manages
> > to perform longword multiplications? ie multiple a long value by
> > another long value? 68000 only has mulu.w. !  ???

The old 8 bit chips didn't have multiply or divide instructions at all, just
add and subtract and bit shifts. We're spoiled these days.

However, what I'd like to know is which assembler mult and div instructions are
the best to use and which to avoid - some of them require 040/060 emulation
don't they? I want to assemblerarise some blitz procedures, but I want to avoid 
these emulated instructions.

If the answer is too complicated, can I find it on the net? My assembly books
are all old 68000/020 only.

Cheers
Mike Child



@ENDNODE
