 rights to use. Then they can concentrate on making good games instead. O=
r at least, that's the theory. In practice, however, when using someone e=
lses "engine" you can never do anything he hasn't thought of (and since y=
ou spent all that money on the original engine, you can't affor to pay a =
programmer taylor it to suit your needs), thus killing invention.


