Yes, here is an improved one.

It will allow you to read all Blitz libraries, including DefLibs and
AcidLibs, and all the ones in Amigalibs/  as well.

Also it can send output to console window, printer, or disk.

It can also be used as a TED "plugin" by calling from the SuperTed menu w=
ith
the argument "TED"

No docs yet, but it should be self-explanatory I hope...

It needs ReqTools, and I recommend KingCON (but not required)

