Hello,

    We are working on a program, unfortunatly, it`s developed a
50-70k memory leak (IE, it`s not freeing 50-70K of chip mem on
exiting). And I know this is my fault, although..

I`m just wondering if anybody knows the name of that program that
you run and specify an EXE as the perameter (it`s just an ikle
CLI program). And it then runs the program as usual, when it exits
it gives you a screen of stats, that tell you what was and wasn`t
freed, the memory locations and stuff,.. stack errors and
memory usage.

I had the proggie before, and may still have, but I think I deleted
it... DOH!,. Anyone know of anything similar or the name of the
proggie?

Cya!
