Hi,
 
> On 18-Feb-99, Loki wrote:
> Hello,
> 
>    We are working on a program, unfortunatly, it`s developed a
> 50-70k memory leak (IE, it`s not freeing 50-70K of chip mem on
> exiting). And I know this is my fault, although..

Maybe NOT your fault - If you are using MUI in your program.

On my system, anytime I run a program that uses MUI, some chip memory
disappears from my system, and is not returned unless I re-boot.  And I
don't mean just Blitz-MUI programs, I mean ANY program with a MUI
interface.

So if you use MUI, forget about the memory loss - I think it is normal...

Later...
