*** Forwarded message, originally scripted, transcribed and generally mes=
sed
about with by Toby Zuijdveld on 19-Feb-99 ***

->On my system, anytime I run a program that uses MUI, some chip memory
->disappears from my system, and is not returned unless I re-boot.
->don't mean just Blitz-MUI programs, I mean ANY program with a MUI
->interface.

MUI does reserve and 'remember' any pictures it uses even when mui
windows aren't opened.  I found a simple flush of all libs will free up
a -lot- of mem, when bigger pictures are configured...  I've since gone
back to plain one pen backdrops ;]

