Err, not me  ;)

But it seems to work fine here.  Can you send a bit of code that doesn't
work for you?

Oh, and don't forget - ABSmouse always uses  Hi-res laced screen
co-ordinates, so if for example you are using a 320 x 200 lo-res screen,
ABSMouse 320,200 will put the pointer in the center of the screen, not the
bottom right corner as you would expect... 

