@NODE "Mail_606" "Re: Mouse-disabling"
Date: Mon, 1 Feb 1999 13:01:06 -0800 (PST)
From: Thomas Cobb <thomcobb@yahoo.com>
Subject: Re: Mouse-disabling


---Andreas Falkenhahn <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de> wrote:

> Forbid() only forbids task rescheduling. It won`t lock the whole
system.

It will as long as your task is busy. e.g.

Forbid_
Repeat
Until JoyB(0)=1
Permit_

This will kill the system until the mouse button is pressed.  If you
do a vwait or put your program to sleep it will break the forbid.

	Thom
