@NODE "Mail_629" "Re: MUI Text objects"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 2 Feb 1999 21:46:37 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>
Organization: International House of Mojo
Date: Tue, 2 Feb 1999 21:37:52 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: MUI Text objects

On 2 Feb 99, at 19:15, Peter broke out long enough to write:

> How would I set up an MUI object using "Text.mui", which uses the Big fo=
nt
> setting, and is centrally aligned? I've tried using "/33c", but it just
> prints "Text.mui" inside the object at compile time.

 Isn't that an escapecharacter sequence? Did you mean \33c? Then you'll be=
 
wanting to use Chr$(27) (remembering from last time the number is octal:) 
somewhere in your string, like a$=3DChr$(27)+"c".


[) /\ \/ ][ [)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn


