>>  My program doesn't use the menu functions but it does use gadgets in =
a
>>  window, I also get enforcer hits (2) when the NCloseWindow command is=

>>  used.
> =

> You could use CloseWindow_ (*win) where win is the pointer to the =

> window you opened.  This works because basically NWindows are =

> just normal windows.(You know none of this Blitz NewType stuff)

    No, no, you can't do that ! Else when the program end, it will
try to close a window which doesn't exist anymore as you don't
have informed the NCS than the window has been closed...

    And trying to close a no more existing window gives a....GURU :-D.

    Bye, bye

                        Fred.

