@NODE "Mail_690" "Re: Palett Re-mapping"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
        blitz-list <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sun, 14 Feb 1999 12:48:22 -0500
Subject: Re: Palett Re-mapping

Hi Allan

On 14-Feb-99, Allan Versaevel wrote:
> Hi,
> 
> How does one get a palette from a decoded shapes object to match the
> palette of the current screen ? So the pattern I am going to use in my
> Window will look as close as possible to the original ? I am at a loss on
> this one. Thanks.

You will need to remap it to the current screen's palette.  But I am not
sure if a "decoded" shape has a palette of it's own attached?  You may also
need to include a palette, or set up one with the correct values inside
your program.

You will find an example of remapping on my web site that might be helpful.

Now a question for you - how do you put a pattern in a window?

Later...
-- 
