@NODE "Mail_745" "ReadFile"
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.free-online.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 11 Feb 1999 17:10:37 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: ReadFile

Hi,
   I am trying to create a graphics format of my own, and use Blitz for
encoding and decoding. The problem is that I save out the screenmode
details into a file, using WriteFile. If I read that data back in, in this
order:

Screen width (eg 320)
Screen height (eg 256)
Depth (eg 5)

and then use the Screen command on that data (which has been put into w,h,
and d variables previously) I get a Screen must be at least 320 wide error.

Any solutions?

-- 
