Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:
>
> > That`s my main concern. I DO NOT HAVE A 15Hz monitor. How in blazes c=
an i
> > program this game if i can`t see it? But this way is also very slow :=
((
> =

> It doesn't have to be. Foundation (for example) is done on an inuition
> screen, and is not (from what I've heard) especially slow. Although it
> is true that you have to be more carefull when writing stuff for the
> OS, it doesn't nesecarily mean it must be slower.

If Foundation was done without OS it would be the same speed and
it wouldn't have been as nice to use since it handles a lot
of it's input using the OS so mouse clicks, dragging and key presses
are all queued as OS events.  This is just one of a thousand
advantages of using the OS. Speed doesn't come into the equation,
it`s more about compatability and future proofing -- how else would
it work in WinUAE! ;)

Cheers,

Paul

-- =

