Right, I was trying this out, but I've hit a problem...as usual :)

I'm guessing that I have to open the battclock.resource (OpenResource_)
before calling Read/WriteBattClock, otherwise it just freezes (the program,
not the system).

I ran SnoopDOS to try and see what's happening, and apparently it's
tryng to open "ock.resource"...

I'm wondering if it's because OpenResource_ returns an "APTR" type pointer,
and since I don't have a clue what difference it makes, maybe that's
what's screwing it up...?

Anyone? :)

See ya,
