The stack is used mainly for storing addresses at which programs have
branched to subroutines. When an assembler RTS is executed, the
parameter on the stack is then offloaded to the PC program counter
causing the program flow to return from the subroutine. It may also be
used for storing data temporarily.

I am wondering, if it might be possible to do some kind of naughty asm
