@NODE "Mail_845" "Re: ShapeGadgets"
 (Eudora Internet Mail Server 2.2); Fri, 11 Dec 1998 14:16:54 +0100
Date: Tue, 09 Feb 1999 14:48:54 +0100
From: Manfred Linzner <manfred.linzner@munich.netsurf.de>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: ShapeGadgets
Encoding: 7bit



Curt Esser wrote:
> 
> Hi Gareth
> 
> On 08-Feb-99, Gareth Griffiths wrote:
> > Hi,
> >   I'm writing a program to launch Internet applications like IBrowse and
> > Voyager. I'm using shapegadgets to provide graphical images, and have put
> > in a change imageset option so that you can change the images.
> >
> > However, SOMETIMES, when you change the imageset, the shapegadgets come
> out
> > scrambled.


The solution is easy. On anything above the 020 the GetAShape commands
has problems with the caches. Always place a
CacheClearU_
before and after the getashape and your images wont be corrupted
anymore.

Regards


-- 
