Subject: Shapes! Argh!

This is really starting to annoy me...

I load in a number of shapes (177 to be exact), if I then later on, free
those shapes using a For...Next loop with "Free Shape i" as the command to
free those shapes, it doesn't free them.  They continue to take up space in
memory, then when loading a smalled number of shapes in (24 to be exact) my
CountShapes function reports that there is 177 shapes in memory!
--
Function.l CountShapes{}
    n.l=1
    While Peek.l(Addr Shape(n.l))<>)
        n+1
    Wend
Function Return n
End Function
--
Argh! Help!

