Subject: Re: The LAst Mouse Control Query


A Guy named Loki  had a reply that went like:

> Hello Whee_Cool
>      Hiya, Whee_Cool... ,on 18-Feb-99 you mailed me about: The LAst Mouse
>      Control Query! So I`ma reply`in...
> 
> W>> Hi,
> W>> 
> W>> Right, the last piece of information I am hoping someone can help me
> W>> with, in reguard in mouse controls, is reading when the mouse button
> is W>> clicked. W>> W>> I don't want how to do it in blitz mode
> 
> #JoyB# command m8,.. I`m sure you have docs on this.. there are others
> but JobB will work in blitz and amiga mode :)

This works for the standard amiga mice.  Unfortunatly, a lot of 
people have pc mice plugged in via the serial port (myself included) 
and the old JoyB(0) command doesn`t work.  ( Neither does 
MouseWait or NMouseWait). Just replace Joyb(0) with MButtons 
and it will work.

Steven Croy

 



