I don't even know what a Segment is...

But maybe you are loading a Font for your program?  If you are, and it is=

about this size, the problem is solved.

Once a font is loaded, it belongs to Intuition.  And Intuition will only
free it if it runs out of memory.  Even after your program ends, the font=

remains.  There is no way (that I know) to remove it.  Maybe that Avail
Flush will do it?

