@NODE "Mail_947" "Re: tilde"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Feb 1999 18:50:48 -0500
Subject: Re: tilde

Hi amorel

On 15-Feb-99, amorel wrote:
> When I was trying to add my homepage address to a string var the ~
> character in it gave the error illegal constant expression. Pretty lame I
> think. Anyway I worked around it by doing this:
> 
> var$="http://www.xs4all.nl/"+chr(ascii nr of ~)+"amorel"
> 
> But there gotta be a better way(though it works ok ofcourse I cant stop
> thinking its not the ideal way).

Nope, that's the only way.  Blitz only allows for the "standard" character
set in strings - ie, the white keys on your keyboard except for the "
character that is used to surround strings.  

None of the darker keys, nor any of the Alternate characters.  You'll have
to use chr$(whatever) for any of these.

Later...
-- 


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
