> A while back, Paul Burkey made a little tool that would scan through an
> ASCII Blitz source, and give you a listing of what commands were used, how
> many times each command was used, and which libraries they were in.
> [snip]
> I know how to read through Blitzlibs:  and get the numbers of all the
> libraries that are "living" there.
> 
> But how do you read the token numbers and command names from each Blitz
> library?  I know it is possible - I have a program "stripper" that can do
> this - I just don't know how.

I must admit to my program cheating quite a bit. It used a ready
parsed output of something like stripper. Then it already knew
the names of all the common blitz commands and which libs they
came from and how big each lib was (including system/basic libs). 
This meant it didn`t have to create this database every time it
ran on various systems which would rarely contain the system/basic
libs because not many people have them.

Cheers,

Paul

