> But how do you read the token numbers and command names from each Blitz=

> library?  I know it is possible - I have a program "stripper" that can =
do
> this - I just don't know how.
 =

Well, I tried to do this myself (Paul's lost his source! Doh!), and
I managed to find the command names from .obj libraries - you look
for =FF=FF (ascii 255) and then count 7 bytes after the second =FF for th=
e start
of the command name.

I'd find that and then read Edit$(255) for the name. The next line holds
the parameter description (like you get when you press Help over
a tokenised command).

This seemed to be correct for all the libraries I checked, but I couldn't=

figure out a reliable way to read the commands from the amigalibs =

"blahblah.library1" type libraries though :(

See ya,
-- =

