Well this gave me an idea of fast asm code for this one ;)

(I made some blitz solving previously).

so asm follows: Assumes that this "toke" is in d0

  lsr.w   #8,d0 ; we want only the library number
  add.b   d0,d0 ; multiplication by two
  addx.b  #0,d0 ; and if it overflowed this will add one to make it odd

>  Like I said, I don't know how to get odd/even differances...
>

This tells you how. :)

You could dou it also by testing if the value is larger than $80 if it is=

sub $80  multiply by two and add one else just multiply by two. :)

-- =


