@NODE "Mail_1005" "Re: WB Window Pointer?"
    18 Feb 99 09:35:54 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 18 Feb 1999 09:35:43 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: WB Window Pointer?

On 18 Feb 99, at 1:16, James L Boyd wrote:

> No, I know about setting window /pointers/ - it's/ /window /pointers/ I'=
m
> after ;)
> 
> As in *win.Window kind of thing...

 Ahh sorry, seems I have a problem with the link between my eyes and my br=
ain.

If you don't have a solution, you could try:

WBToScreen 0
*scr.Screen =3D Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
*win.Window =3D *scr\FirstWindow
While *win
    Print Peek$(*win\Title)
    If *win\Flags & #WFLG_WBENCHWINDOW Then NPrint " <WB>" Else NPrint ""
    *win =3D *win\NextWindow
Wend
Clickmouse
End

 This worked OK here.


