On 18-Feb-99, Whee_Cool set out across the seas with this message:

->How do u read the mouse?? or I see is MOUSEX( which is blitz mode

There is also #MouseY# (Blitz mode again) #SmouseX#, #SMouseY#, #WMouseX#=
#WMouseY# and I *think* #EmouseX# and #EmouseY#.

S reads the mouse position from the top left of the currently active scre=
en, W
reads it from the top left of the currently used window and E returns the=

position of where it was at the last Event.  Don't know if it's in relati=
on to
the screen or window tho, and too lazy to check ;]

